<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2025-10-26-summing-up.png" alt="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Denarius_of_Gordian_II_(head).png" width="200" height="267" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-72013" /></p>
<blockquote><p>
Twenty-two acknowledged concubines, and a library of sixty-two thousand volumes, attested the variety of his inclinations; and from the productions which he left behind him, it appears that the former as well as the latter were designed for use rather than for ostentation.
</p></blockquote>
<p>&#8212; Edward Gibbon, on the Roman emperor Gordian II</p>
